quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,16,"And We have already created man and know what his soul whispers to him, and We are closer{1} to him than [his] jugular vein.",1:[In absolute knowledge of everything about him.  "We" has also been interpreted to mean the angels who are mentioned in the following verse.]
  50,17,"When the two receivers [i.e., recording angels] receive,{1} seated on the right and on the left.",1:[And record each word and deed.]
  50,18,"He [i.e., man] utters no word except that with him is an observer prepared [to record]."
  51,10,"Destroyed are the misinformers{1}",1:[Or "May they be destroyed" or "cursed."]
  51,11,"Who are within a flood [of confusion] and heedless."
  51,12,"They ask, "
  52,1,"By the mount"
  52,2,"And [by] a Book inscribed{1}",1:[Interpreted as the Preserved Slate or possibly the Qur’ān.]
  52,3,"In parchment spread open"